  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\nNo response received there and hence posting here\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI am working on a Dapp with private smart-contracts + quorum. Does truffle's testing framework support connecting to multiple networks from within the test code (not from the command-line)? The tutorial here: http://truffleframework.com/tutorials/building-dapps-for-quorum-private-enterprise-blockchains does that from the truffle console, but I would like to do the same (execute contract calls as different nodes - by connecting to different 'networks') from within a test method. Possible?\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nNA\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nAbility to specify network names from within a test method for both contract deployments and other transactions\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nNot sure if it is possible today. Might be an enhancement\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows 10\r\n* Ethereum client: Quorum 2.0.2\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v4.1.6 (core: 4.1.6)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v8.11.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  5.6.0\r\n",
